<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<Project Sdk="Microsoft.NET.Sdk">
  <PropertyGroup>
    <TargetFramework>net40</TargetFramework>
    <Title>PeterHan.PLib</Title>
    <AssemblyTitle>PeterHanLib</AssemblyTitle>
    <Version>3.14.1.0</Version>
    <!--<PackageVersion>3.14.1-beta</PackageVersion>-->
    <UsesPLib>false</UsesPLib>
    <Authors>Peter Han (https://github.com/peterhaneve)</Authors>
    <PackageProjectUrl>https://github.com/peterhaneve/ONIMods</PackageProjectUrl>
    <PackageLicenseExpression>MIT</PackageLicenseExpression>
    <PackageIcon>icon.png</PackageIcon>
    <PackageTags>Game, OxygenNotIncluded, Oxygen, PLib, Library</PackageTags>
    <GeneratePackageOnBuild>true</GeneratePackageOnBuild>
    <Copyright>Copyright 2021 Peter Han</Copyright>
    <Description>PLib - Peter Han's library used for creating mods for Oxygen Not Included, a simulation game by Klei Entertainment.
    
Contains methods aimed at improving cross-mod compatibility, in-game user interfaces, and game-wide functions such as Actions and Lighting. An easy-to-use Mod Options menu is also included.</Description>
    <PackageReleaseNotes>Version 3.14 will load on both DLC and Vanilla if properly merged.

Add nullable int and float to PLib Options. Options in nested classes that are used in properties will now be included in the UI.

Tool icons can now be registered in a DLC/Vanilla independent manner, as well as building technologies for buildings outside of PBuilding.</PackageReleaseNotes>
    <RootNamespace>PeterHan.PLib</RootNamespace>
    <AssemblyVersion>3.14.1.0</AssemblyVersion>
    <GenerateAssemblyFileVersionAttribute>false</GenerateAssemblyFileVersionAttribute>  
    <GenerateAssemblyInformationalVersionAttribute>false</GenerateAssemblyInformationalVersionAttribute>
    <DistributeMod>false</DistributeMod>
  </PropertyGroup>
  <PropertyGroup Condition=" '$(Configuration)' == 'Release' ">
    <DocumentationFile>bin\Release\PLib.xml</DocumentationFile>
  </PropertyGroup>
  <ItemGroup>
    <None Include="icon.png" Pack="True" PackagePath="" />
  </ItemGroup>
</Project>
